Many Linux users like to read their mails in text mail user agents:
they are the traditional hacker choice, are easy to use remotely and
offer other advantages too. But how to use them efficiently in
comparison with e.g. modern webmails like gmail? That means fast
fulltext search in large mailboxes, easy tracking of bushy threads, etc.
First, we will show interesting uses of the 'limit' command in mutt,
mainly together with the fulltext mail indexer notmuch. An open
discussion on alternatives, interesting MUA features and other ideas
will follow.
